CSS Units

font-size
    rem - 1=16px Relative to font-size of the root element, will adapt to changes on user side 

    a tip, set html to font-size:62.5%
    then 1 rem = 10 px

width

1ch - equals to the width of a character
usually it no more than 75ch per line for readability, sometimes less

height, use min-height 

vh, %, rm

padding/margin

rem
em - Relative to the font-size of the element

Use relative units
